@BRWesty 
This is from the NYT article by Vaughn. 
A quick note: I omitted the vanilla oil featured in the original, so I added vanilla extract to our version to capture the flavor. But if you want to make the oil at home, just scrape the beans from a vanilla pod into a small saucepan with ¼ cup each of olive oil and neutral oil, and let it simmer for a few minutes before taking it off the heat. Let it cool, et voilà!

